cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving cache systems for video-on-demand and video-sharing platforms in terms of traffic reduction on the core network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video content and its popularity. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a LRU cache replacement policy and characterizes its performance. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper uses the notion of audience retention rate, which is a measure of the popularity of different parts of the same video content. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to caching and video content.
